---

## 1. RelatedPosts placement in ContentView.jsx

File: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\ContentViewer\ContentView.jsx`

The structure from the closing `</article>` tag outward (lines 629-668):

```jsx
                            <div className="cv-body">
                                {postData?.postType === 'canvas' ? (
                                    <CanvasViewer canvasDoc={postData?.canvasDoc} />
                                ) : (
                                    <LexicalComposer initialConfig={{ ... }}>
                                        <RichTextPlugin
                                            contentEditable={<ContentEditable />}
                                            ErrorBoundary={LexicalErrorBoundary}
                                        />
                                    </LexicalComposer>
                                )}
                            </div>
                        </>
                    )}
                </article>

                <RelatedPosts journalId={postData?.journalId} />

                {/* Toast notification */}
                <AnimatePresence>
                    {(bookmarkedMessage) && (
                        <motion.div
                            className="cv-toast"
                            initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 8 }}
                            animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
                            exit={{ opacity: 0, y: 8 }}
                            transition={{ duration: 0.2, ease: "easeOut" }}
                        >
                            {bookmarkedMessage}
                        </motion.div>
                    )}
                </AnimatePresence>
            </div>
```

Key structural facts:
- `<RelatedPosts>` is a **direct sibling** of `<article className="cv-article">`, both direct children of `<div className="cv-container">`.
- There is **no wrapper div** between `</article>` and `<RelatedPosts>`. The gap between them is entirely controlled by CSS (`cv-body` margin-bottom + `rp-section` margin-top).
- `<RelatedPosts>` receives only the `journalId` prop — no post data passed down.

---

## 2. Data fields returned by the SQL RPC and service

File: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\server\sql\discovery.sql`

The `find_related_posts` function's `RETURNS TABLE` declaration (lines 14-28):

```sql
RETURNS TABLE (
    id UUID,
    title TEXT,
    content JSONB,       -- <-- full Lexical JSON state, NOT an excerpt
    post_type TEXT,
    canvas_doc JSONB,    -- <-- full canvas doc for canvas-type posts
    created_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
    user_id UUID,
    user_name TEXT,
    user_image_url TEXT,
    user_badge TEXT,
    username TEXT,
    semantic_similarity FLOAT,
    hot_score BIGINT,
    composite_score FLOAT
)
```

**Critical point on text content:** `content` and `canvas_doc` are returned as raw JSONB — these are the full Lexical editor state / canvas documents. There is **no pre-generated excerpt, snippet, or truncated text field**. No `excerpt`, `summary`, or `body_text` column exists in the returned shape.

File: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\server\services\discoveryService.js`

The service passes raw RPC results straight through with no field mapping or excerpt extraction. It only applies confidence-tier capping (lines 76-88):

```js
return {
    posts: cappedPosts,   // each post has all the fields above verbatim
    confidence: tier.label,
    topSimilarity,
};
```

File: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\API\Api.js` (lines 1417-1430):

```js
export const getRelatedPosts = async (journalId) => {
    if (!journalId) return { posts: [], confidence: 'none', topSimilarity: 0 };

    const response = await apiRequest(`${BASE_URL}/journal/${encodeURIComponent(journalId)}/related`, {
        method: 'GET',
    });

    if (!response.ok) {
        const error = await response.json().catch(() => ({}));
        throw new Error(error?.error || 'failed to fetch related posts');
    }

    return await response.json();
}
```

The client does **zero transformation** — it returns the JSON body verbatim. So the full shape each related post object has on the client is:

```
{
  id, title, content, post_type, canvas_doc,
  created_at, user_id, user_name, user_image_url,
  user_badge, username, semantic_similarity, hot_score, composite_score
}
```

**What the RelatedPostCard component actually uses** (from `RelatedPosts.jsx`):

```
post.id               → navigation target (/home/post/:id)
post.title            → displayed as card title (2-line clamp)
post.user_image_url   → avatar
post.user_name        → author name
post.user_badge       → VerifiedBadge
post.created_at       → formatted date
post.semantic_similarity → accent opacity calculation
```

The `content`, `canvas_doc`, `post_type`, `hot_score`, `composite_score`, `user_id`, and `username` fields are **received but not consumed at all** by the current RelatedPostCard UI. There is no excerpt rendering anywhere.

