## 3. .cv-article CSS (and spacing context)

File: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\ContentViewer\contentviewer.css`

```css
/* Container — flex column, centered */
.cv-container {
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 100vh;
    background-color: var(--bg-primary);
    overflow-y: auto;
}

/* Article — the post itself */
.cv-article {
    max-width: 620px;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 0 24px;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    /* NO margin-bottom defined here */
}

/* Post body — last element inside article */
.cv-body {
    margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 80px;   /* <-- 80px gap from body bottom to article bottom */
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    ...
}

/* Responsive overrides */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cv-article { max-width: 100%; padding: 0 24px; }
}
@media (max-width: 480px) {
    .cv-article { padding: 0 16px; padding-bottom: 2rem; }
    .cv-body    { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 60px; }
}
```

File: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Discovery\RelatedPosts.css`

```css
.rp-section {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;       /* gap from article bottom edge */
    padding-top: 1.5rem;      /* internal padding above content, below border */
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    max-width: 620px;         /* matches .cv-article */
    width: 100%;
    padding-left: 24px;       /* matches .cv-article */
    padding-right: 24px;
    box-sizing: border-box;
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
    .rp-section {
        margin-top: 2rem;
        padding-top: 1.25rem;
        padding-left: 16px;
        padding-right: 16px;
    }
}
```

**Effective spacing between visible content and RelatedPosts:**

- The last real content element is `.cv-body` which has `margin-bottom: 80px` (or `60px` on mobile).
- `.cv-article` itself has no `margin-bottom`.
- `.rp-section` adds another `margin-top: 2.5rem` (40px) on top of that, plus a `border-top` line and `padding-top: 1.5rem` (24px) before the heading.

So the total vertical gap from the bottom of the post body text to the "Posts you might like" heading is: **80px (cv-body margin-bottom) + 40px (rp-section margin-top) + 1px border + 24px (rp-section padding-top) = ~145px** at full width. On mobile (480px), it's 60 + 32 + 1 + 20 = ~113px.

